<item>
            <title>[SOLR-2912] File descriptor leak in ShowFileRequestHandler.getFileContents()</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-2912</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There is a file descriptor leak in ShowFileRequestHandler.getFileContents() - the InputStream is not closed. This could cause a &quot;Too many open files&quot; error if the admin page is loaded a lot.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve only tested this on 3.2, but I think it affects all recent versions, including trunk.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12532479">SOLR-2912</key>
            <summary>File descriptor leak in ShowFileRequestHandler.getFileContents()</summary>
